dc_title_s: PSAP Service Area Boundaries Waupaca County, WI 2020
dc_description_s: This data layer represents 911 Public Safety Answering Point (PSAP) service area boundaries in Waupaca county, Wisconsin in 2020. According to the National Emergency Number Association (NENA), a Public Safety Answering Point (PSAP) is a facility equipped and staffed to receive 9-1-1 calls. The service area is the geographic area within which a 911 call placed using a landline is answered at the associated PSAP. [The data set represents the jurisdictional boundaries for the various units of local government within Waupaca County, Wisconsin. The data is represented using polygons stored in a Geodatabase. The data is updated annually.]
